  "plainText": "Exclusive to:\nCork\nFood Info\n10\n10\n0\nWood\n(non-survivor food)\nObject Info\n+5\n45 sec\n20\nSource\nDropped by\nMiscellaneous\n\"cork\"\n“Science says it floats.”\n–Wilson\n“Still sets on fire.”\n–Willow\n“Is from funny tree.”\n–Wolfgang\n“It floats. Like a dead body.”\n–Wendy\n“MAINTAINS A CURIOUS RELATIONSHIP WITH MY ENEMY”\n–WX-78\n“Material from the Quercus Suber.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“It came from that weird tree.”\n–Woodie\n“A boyant material.”\n–Maxwell\n“A lightweight, hydrophobic material.”\n–Wagstaff\n“A material with many uses!”\n–Wigfrid\n“I bet we can make something with this.”\n–Webber\n“Bet this'll float.”\n–Walani\n“If only there were a wine bottle to put this in.”\n–Warly\n“'Tis barely seaworthy.”\n–Woodlegs\n“DOST HARDLY WEIGH A BIT”\n–Wilba\n“Wood? Not wood”\n–Wormwood\n“A light material but not sturdy enough to make a balloon with.”\n–Wheeler\nCork is a resource exclusive to the Hamlet DLC. It can be gathered by chopping down Claw Palm Trees and is required for several Crafting recipes.\nCork can also be used to repair Wood Walls and to refuel Cork Candle Hats.\nUsage[edit | edit source]\n×4\n×2\n×3\n×2\n×6\n×3\n×3\n×3\n×3\n×2\n×4\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nCork originally had red leaves, but the color was changed in the Quality of Life update.\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nThe old design of Cork.\nView or edit this template\nResources\nAttention: The following categories are only for the players look up the page based on their first impression, they have nothing to do with the actual categories/behavior/function/tags of these items\nPlants\nNatural non-living materials\nMobs Parts\nSkins\nFeathers\nBones and horns\nGems\nShadow Resources\nLunar Resources\nCraftable Resources\nNon-natural materials\nTrinkets\nLost Relics\nTransmission Items",
